</i><hr size="1" /></blockquote>This is where your argument fails. Not all Gates and above Shaman have several hundred aa's. The way that Gates and above shaman have been able to get to that position is flags Blazz, not time spent in game. It's been about Advancement and reward based on flagging. If you want to make Gates and above shaman effective you need to enable them to be effective without telling them to take 6 months off raiding and grind 200 aa then come back.<blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />Originally Posted by <b>Blazz</b><br /><i><br />
Advancement and reward based on time. That is EQ. <br />
</i><hr size="1" /></blockquote>No. It is not EQ.<blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />Originally Posted by <b>Blazz</b><br /><i><br />
I seriously see you people that disagree with me as the BIGGEST part of the problem. You want more for less. You want rewards without dedication. You want Diablo 2, where anyone can log in for 5 minutes and be maxxed out. You want total equality with the guy who plays 5 times as much as you do. <br />
</i><hr size="1" /></blockquote>Its an alarming way to head through life thinking that anyone who disagrees with you is the problem.</p>
	
	
	
	
	
