<tr>
	<td class="alt2" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>Blazz</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Mystic<br />
		
	
	<br />
	Joined: Sep 2003<br />
	Location: Upstate, NY
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>After giving this some thought, I have come up with a few paths for other classes as well.<br />
<br />
Clerics - Better soloing tools (double attack, snare), or bigger nukes, or better buffing (increased spell haste, AC and hps on their buffs).<br />
<br />
Warriors - More AC, more +avoid, strikethourhg, etc effect, or more DPS output.<br />
<br />
Knights - better AC, more avoind, strikethrough, etc, a mini defensive AA, more DPS<br />
<br />
Necros - summon pet items, more nuking DPS, a group buff that matters, AE hp/mana regen<br />
<br />
Druids - better pet, better nuking focus, an HoT.<br />
<br />
Enchanters - Better pet, pet commands, better DOTs or better Nukes. <br />
<br />
Rogues - more soloing tools<br />
<br />
Wizards - toughie, they are kinda at the top of what they do. What do wizards want? More mana? More crits?<br />
<br />
Monks - Better DPS, better avoidancce, etc etc<br />
<br />
Mages - better pet items (no-drop of course), bigger nukes (tough one, though, they are close to wizards now arent they?) not sure, never really looked at the class.<br />
<br />
Remember, I am suggesting these be SUPER EXPENSIVE AA, the kind that you choose and thats where you are as a character. It would offer variations on each class in the "definitive EQ roles" of healing, tanking, and DPS. <br />
<br />
I dunno, I just cannot come up with many other solutions without TOTALLY re-doing a few classes COMPLETELY, seriously. I want solutions that are available to everyone. I want rewards based on time spent progressing (getting XP is progress). Heck people are argueing that the Raiders do not have time to XP as much, well tough. Make time, or dont be as effective. Suddenly the guy who chooses not to raid can be nearly as effective as the guy with 27 days played that got into a Time+ guild and got tons of drops in the 2nd week of membership because they were gonna rot anyway. <br />
<br />
I dunno. Got no answers to the problems. Someone on another thread said changes to one class effect balance with many other classes. We are a perfect example of that. BLs and Chanters are able to slow as well as we can, the differences are totally negligible. Our DOTs are not effective, and we havent gotten tools to keep up with the need for fast DPS, like Necro, Rangers and Monks did. Our healing looks like a drop of rain in a Lake of mob DPS. <br />
<br />
Jacks of all trades, Masters of Trivial Content.</p>
	
	
	
